-- Sears to raise up to $625 mln through notes offering
-- By Sruthi Ramakrishnan in Bangalore
-- Mon Oct 20, 2014 06:42AM EDT
-- None



Oct 20 (Reuters) - Struggling retailer Sears Holdings Corp <SHLD.O> said it would raise up to $625 million through a rights offering of senior notes due 2019 and warrants to buy shares.

Sears Chief Executive Eddie Lampert and his hedge fund, ESL Investments Inc and certain affiliated funds, plan to exercise their rights, the company said in a statement. [ID:nPn1CMTmY]